![Invincible-Braces](data:image/png;base64, "Invincible Braces")



Have you ever heard the saying tin grins are in. This, of course, refers to a smile full of metal bands, brackets, and wires or in other words[traditional braces](http://blog.doctorbase.com/index.php/2009/07/14/what-is-involved-in-getting-braces-aka-orthodontics/ "Braces: What is Involved in Getting Braces (aka Orthodontics)?"). But what if you want[straighter teeth without the anyone ever knowing](http://blog.doctorbase.com/index.php/2009/07/15/clear-braces-what-are-the-choices-and-cost/ "Clear Braces - What are the Choices and Cost?")? If this sounds perfect to you, then you will be interested in learning more about Invisalign.

The Invisalign method consists of a series of thermoplastic clear aligners that are custom made for you. They move your teeth in the sequence recommended by your dentist. You change the aligners every 2 weeks, and visit your dentist every 4-6 weeks for an exam. Typical treatment time is about a year, though it varies from patient to patient.
